*.mpq !text !filter !merge !diff

# Windows-bound files served by raw.github.com to the launcher's repair
# pipeline. The launcher writes the downloaded bytes as-is, and several
# downstream consumers expect CRLF on Windows:
#   - D2 1.10f's TXT data parser CRASHES on LF (Fog.dll NULL deref)
#   - cmd.exe historically chokes on LF .bat files
#   - D2GL / ddraw INI parsers may quietly ignore LF settings
#
# `-text` tells git to NOT normalize line endings — store and serve the
# exact bytes committed. We commit these as CRLF so raw serves CRLF.
# (`eol=crlf` alone doesn't help — that only affects working-tree
# checkout; raw.github.com still serves the LF-normalized blob.)
game/data/global/excel/*.txt -text
game/data/local/lng/eng/*.txt -text
game/data/local/LNG/ENG/*.txt -text
game/**/*.ini -text
game/**/*.bat -text

# Binary D2 assets — never normalize line endings
*.tbl binary
*.bin binary
*.dc6 binary
*.ds1 binary
*.dt1 binary
*.cof binary
*.d2s binary
